\n<Innkeeper>Your room is the VIP room at the very back. We've been paid
a hefty sum in advance, so feel free to stay as many nights
as you like. Even if you say you're leaving soon, I won't be
giving a refund.

\n<Innkeeper>Calling it shabby? You should be grateful there's even a
roof over your head. The little one sure complains a lot.
B

\n<Innkeeper>"If something gets stolen, I don't know anything about it.
It's the fault of the one who got robbed. It's their own
fault for not being careful."

\n<Innkeeper>"My job? I'm just here drinking. I don't know anything about
what happens around here."
C

\n<Innkeeper>Hey, kitty brat. Wanna try my new dish? It's the old lady's
special lunch set.
Absolutely not.
If it's just a bite.
I'll eat it later.

\n<Innkeeper>You won't die from it, how rude. The youth these days don't

\n<Old Man>Hey, don't just barge in here, cat. I'll make a stew out of
you and eat you up.

\n<Peddler>Even in such a filthy town, as long as there's human
activity, there will be demand and supply. There are plenty
of business opportunities.

\n<Peddler>Compared to the royal capital Anis, where they take
ridiculous tariffs, this dump is far better.

I ended up spending quite a bit of money on lodging. Let's
earn some back with quests. I suddenly feel like I've grown
up!

Washing dirty clothes in dirty water, getting them even
dirtier.

A strong smell of alcohol... I feel like I could get drunk
just by being near it.
There's a lot of alcohol in it.

parameters.name: 探索15(セキュリティホール)

parameters:
This is a diary since I arrived. Maybe I should check what
I've done. (Days passed \v[516] Guild Rank \v[1007])
Guild Requests
About the Guild Members
About the Townspeople
Other Matters
That's enough
ギルドの依頼
Let's check the status of the requests.

The investigation request for Galette Cave... In the middle
of it, Lynx was attacked and saved by Kunes. The
investigation was completed, but I feel terrible.
There's nothing to check, I haven't done anything yet!

I was able to defeat a succubus calling herself Megna. (She
escaped though) But to feel such strange emotions...
Normally, I would have easily won against such a creature!

Just thinking about Megna makes my chest hurt... I want to
see her. But I have to work. I need to level up...

I'm so in love with Megna, I can't stand it! I need to
quickly offer lots of EXP and make her strong enough so she
won't be killed by humans...

I defeated Megna. Cutting down a monster that looks human
feels disgusting. But I definitely did the right thing! It's
good that I took her down before she could harm others.

I managed to repel a monster named Latier. But that sweet
scent still lingers in my nose! It almost drove me crazy. I
need to stay focused!

As a result, I ended up being spared by Latier. After what
happened, next time... I might not be able to fight.

Even though Lynx and Kunes were killed... I know it's
terrible, but... I'll probably end up going to see Latier
again.

I was able to avenge Lynx and Kunes. If only I had moved
faster at that time, both could have been saved. I need to
strengthen my resolve!

The request to find a dead husband seems to have been a
scheme by Sister Soel. I reported it, but... I wonder if
they'll believe me?

The ruins investigation is complete! Yay! The treasure was
just a white bottle... What is it used for?

The ruins investigation was completed, but I had a dispute
with Bijou and the contents of the treasure were
destroyed... Such a pity. What was the liquid in that broken
bottle?

I guarded the house of Count Noblesse in the noble district
Lumare! I cornered the phantom thief, but due to various
things, they got away! It's embarrassing, so this is a
secret!

I feel bad for Count Noblesse, but give up on the Howling
Stone! They're rich, so they can just buy a new one. It's
wrong for them to try to live such good lives all by
themselves!

But maybe the Catfield house is no different. Coming here
made me realize how privileged I've been. There must still
be so much that I don't know!

I finally caught the phantom thief! It turns out the Howling
Stone was a fake from the start. They really pulled one over
on us.

Even though it's a fake, it seems to be quite valuable. That
means the count was serious too.

Jean's mother, Mare-san, was an imposter! I don't know what
kind of monster she was, but her body melted like mud. I
must rescue Jean quickly...!

I couldn't kill Mare-san. Whether this was the right thing
or not, I don't know. But... let's stop thinking about it
anymore.

Doing lewd things with Mare-san is absolutely forbidden.
She's already a monster. So this has to be the last time.
Otherwise...

I defeated Mare-san's imposter. Jean seems convinced and has
decided to live strongly. But did I really do the right
thing? It's troubling.

When I spilled that white bottle, the monster aura
disappeared from Mare-san! Her body can't return to its
original form, but her heart is truly Mare-san's! I hope she
continues to live happily with Jean! So glad!

Mare-san regained her human heart, which is good, but she
became incredibly aggressive... It can't be helped, but she
drained me completely!

I went to exterminate a high-ranking imp but... Ah, no
good-. I can't write such things in a diary! I lied and said
the request was completed.

I did something indecent with an imp again... Even though I
know it's a monster. There's no way I could endure that...

I exterminated the high-ranking imp. To think that even imps
have turned into succubi! What on earth is the Demon King
thinking? Maybe they're a pervert.

I couldn't defeat Arno... Why did I do such a thing? But it
might happen again.

Even though I might be killed someday, I'm going back to
Arno to be drained again. It might be hopeless.

I defeated Arno, the succubus! She was doing ecological
research disguised as a human! But it's scary that monsters
have infiltrated even inside the town.

I beat those weird succubi duo Sheika and Barley. They
almost escaped but there won't be a next time! The audience
threw alcohol at me. Annoying!

I defeated Party People! It was so loud my ears almost went
bad! The audience was angry, but they should be grateful
their lives were saved! Both alcohol and succubi ruin
people! Ahh! What a loss helping them!

I thought about taking down Sheika and Barley but... after
what they did... I can't endure it. Even though I know it's
absolutely wrong.

Those two drained me dry in front of everyone... Such an
embarrassing thing, even though I hate it! Despite hating
it, maybe it was the most exciting thing ever...
ギルドの人たちについて

The Guild Master seemed really unpleasant at first but
became suddenly kind once we became comrades. Maybe they're
unexpectedly soft on insiders!

Kunes is said to be the strongest in the guild. His beard,
bandana, and husky voice are so cool.

Kunes was taken down by Latier right before my eyes. If only
I had been a little faster, maybe he could have been
saved... But let's stop thinking about it now.

Lynx is said to be among the top three strongest in the
guild! He seems to be a wizard who wields wind magic. He
appears to have some issues with alcohol and women.

Lynx was eaten by a succubus in the Galette Cave.
Remembering how people were... it makes me feel strange.

Dodon was the first old man who sexually harassed me.
Despite his appearance, he seems to be quite capable in
battle, but I wonder. He's big, but he seems weak.

Bijou is an adult woman with glasses. She specializes in
treasure hunting rather than monster hunting. But I can feel
her high fire and water magic power!

I was suddenly made to drink a strange medicine by Bijou! To
think she would do such a thing... I was off guard... she's
someone I better not get too close to!

Bijou challenged me to a revenge match. I won the fight
but... I feel like I've lost terribly. I better not get
close to her again... but...

I was defeated and revenged by Bijou. After what she did...
ugh, just remembering it... if I have money and go to the
second floor of the guild, then again...

Ugh... I was drained again by Bijou... I feel like my mind
is going crazy. If such things happen over and over...

I've already contributed over 30,000G to Bijou... Once you
know that pleasure, you can't go back. I'm sorry.

Scheibel is a bright woman. She seems to live helping the
Guild Master. She smells a bit like alcohol.

Lakra is a slightly pretentious adventurer. But adventurers
are cooler when they're pretentious. Because they're
adventurers after all.

Annie is a hearty person with no deceit. She seems to smash
monsters with her hammer. She feels like a reliable big
sister.

Lintei seems like a very decent older brother. He always
tries to judge things calmly. But he eats weird smelling
rice.
町の人たちについて

This town is called Dreamne. It's a slum located inside a
large hole that suddenly appeared in the noble district of
Lumare. The security doesn't seem very good...

Radro is an energetic and cute person who runs an orphanage.
She seems to be taking care of six children all by herself.
Amazing! She's kind and smells good.

I never imagined that Radro was the true identity of the
phantom thief "L"... She's doing such reckless things for
the children. But I'm really glad I didn't catch her.

There were some embarrassing things, but... let's keep that
between us and lock it away in our hearts. I have to show my
face at the orphanage too.

I donated a lot to the orphanage! The children seem happy
with the various things they were able to buy! It's a bit
embarrassing, but I'm happy!

Radro is a very important person to me! I've decided to
protect her no matter what! The most precious treasure I
found since coming here!

It seems Radro has suddenly disappeared. I'm worried. Where
could she be... I'll search as much as I can between
requests.

I feel sorry for the children at the orphanage. Is there
anything I can do to help... I understand the loneliness of
not having a mother.

Soel is a gentle woman who works as a sister at the church.
She seems to be working hard to spread the teachings of Sage
Storm. But apparently, there aren't many proper believers.

I never imagined that the sister was manipulating corpses
with necromancy... I reported it to the guild, but they
didn't believe me much. Now she seems to be barricaded in
the church with a special barrier.

Necromancy is a taboo forbidden by magical law. It's merely
a technique for manipulating corpses, not magic for
resurrection. If there were magic for resurrection, it would
surely be an extension of healing magic.

I lost to Soel's words and stopped reporting her. If no one
knows, it'll be fine. As long as no one finds out...

I lost to Soel's temptation again... Such a terrible person,
I'm supposed to hate her... I hate her so much. But I can't
resist.

I hate Soel so much... yet I came inside her again... I hate
this. I'm starting to hate myself. And yet, I already want
to see her again even as I write this.

I caught Soel and had her put in jail. The textbook said
that necromancy is taboo because it cheapens the value of
death and leads to the breakdown of the heart.

I believe that if Soel cools her head in jail, she will
surely become calm. At heart, I want to believe she's a kind
person. But we'll probably never meet again...
その他のこと

The fastest way to find my sister is to become an
adventurer! Things went well, but I ran out of money for
lodging! Might as well work on guild jobs and earn some
money!

The book found in the ruins was partly unreadable, but it
probably studied how to exorcise demons that possess people.
That treasure might just be...

Grandpa came! He looked a bit tired. Once everything is
over, I thought about being kinder to him.

I went to the noble district! It's a beautiful town, but the
Catfield house is just as beautiful, so it wasn't that fresh
of an experience!

Suddenly there was a flood of requests! There seem to be
some that are direct nominations. As an adventurer, have I
become somewhat respectable?

The innkeeper lady gave me a lunch plate. If I eat this,
I'll surely die. You can tell by looking at it. You can tell
by the smell too. Sorry to say this about food, but let's
use this as a weapon.
もういいや
It's Wanz's diary! Should I read it?
Read it anyway
Don't read it
読んじゃう

I've become an adventurer! I don't have any real combat
experience, but I've trained thoroughly with \n[1], so I'm
sure I'll be fine fighting monsters!

The bed is too hard, and the room is too small! There's a
strange smell, and the snoring from the other rooms is loud!
Ugh... But I'll endure it!

\n[1] is working hard too! I can't lose to them, so I'll do
my best! I can't lose to my younger sibling!

I thought I heard rustling noises at night, and it turned
out to be the landlady sneaking into my room trying to touch
my belongings! I screamed thinking it was a ghost! For some
reason, I got scolded!

At the garbage dump, someone unluckily got hit by trash and
seems to have died. The person throwing it should have
looked below! I thought the person living above was a bit
too cruel!

I wonder if grandpa is getting scolded... Is everyone
worried...? I'm starting to feel a bit guilty. But I can't
go back yet.

Grandpa finally came! But he wasn't angry at all, which was
a relief! He asked about my sister and various things... I
think grandpa was really troubled too.

It's been 7 days since I arrived here. There's no
information about my sister. My sister...

Speaking of which, my sister used to have various friends in
the past. A rough kid, a dirty kid, a cute kid, a smart-
looking kid, a bad-looking kid... Humans, beastfolk,
everyone adored my sister.

We were always just studying and training, so we didn't have
friends, but my sister would secretly come to my room and
tell me stories, which was the highlight of my day.

I gave some money to a beggar and got complained at! They
said 10G was too little. Sure, that's true, but it's better
than 0! Why do I get scolded for increasing it from 0 to
10?!

I've developed the habit of being vigilant so as not to get
robbed. It's a necessary skill to live in this town, but
honestly, I don't want to suspect anyone!

At first, I thought this was an unpleasant town, but now I
understand that everyone is working hard in their own way. I
wouldn't have realized this if I had stayed home studying.

Apparently there was a fight at the guild. It's full of
drunkards, so it's a common occurrence. I hate the smell of
alcohol!

I'm starting to get used to life here. There are bad people,
but there are also good people. That's probably the same
anywhere in the world.
やめとく
It's Louie's diary! Should I take a peek?
Read it anyway
Don't read it
読んじゃう

I thought becoming an adventurer would make it easier to
catch wind of my sister's rumors, but this place seems a bit
closed off. Still, I should at least try doing some work!

The bed is too hard, and the room is too cramped! There's a
weird smell, and the snoring from the other rooms is loud!
Ugh... But I'll endure it!

It seems \n[1] is also handling guild tasks! I can't lose
to them! As their older sibling!

I thought I heard rustling in the middle of the night, and
it turned out to be the landlady sneaking into my room
trying to tamper with my belongings! What a hag! I'll have
to set up a simple barrier on the door before I sleep!

I wonder if grandpa is being scolded... Is everyone
worried...? I'm starting to feel a bit guilty. But I can't
go back yet.

Someone apparently died after being hit by 'heaven's
blessing' (trash thrown from above). This is definitely not
right! This town... and the town above...

Grandpa finally came! But he wasn't angry at all, which was
a relief! I asked about my sister and various things... I
also think father's way of thinking is wrong.

It's been 7 days since I arrived here. No information about
my sister has come in. But there's been no pursuit from home
either, so there's still time.

Come to think of it, my sister used to have all sorts of
friends back in the day. Rough kids, dirty kids, cute kids,
smart-looking kids, bad kids... Both humans and beastfolk,
everyone adored my sister.

Adored might not be the right word; maybe she was more like
a bossy leader. Father said not to become like that, but
honestly, I've always been envious.

I gave some money to a beggar and got complained at!
Annoyed, I used sleight of hand to steal back what was in
their pocket! Idiot!

I've developed the habit of staying alert so as not to get
robbed. It's a necessary skill for living in this town, but
truthfully, I don't want to suspect anyone!

At first, I thought this was an unpleasant town, but now I
understand that everyone is just trying their best in their
own way. I wouldn't have realized this if I had stayed home
studying.

There seems to have been a fight at the guild. It's full of
drunks, so it happens often. The master was laughing his
head off about it. This place is hopeless.

I'm starting to get used to life here. Even the smell of
alcohol and the stench of the sewers.
やめとく
